{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.11",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 11 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:1",
      "text": "False balances are an abomination before the Lord: but a just weight is acceptable unto him.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:2",
      "text": "Wherever pride enters, there will be also disgrace: but the mouth of the lowly meditates wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:3",
      "text": "When a just man dies he leaves regret: but the destruction of the ungodly is speedy, and causes joy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:5",
      "text": "Righteousness traces out blameless paths: but ungodliness encounters unjust dealing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:6",
      "text": "The righteousness of upright men delivers them: but transgressors are caught in their own destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:7",
      "text": "At the death of a just man his hope does not perish: but the boast of the ungodly perishes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:8",
      "text": "A righteous man escapes from a snare, and the ungodly man is delivered up in his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:9",
      "text": "In the mouth of ungodly men is a snare to citizens: but the understanding of righteous men is prosperous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:10",
      "text": "In the prosperity of righteous men a city prospers:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:11",
      "text": "but by the mouths of ungodly men it is overthrown.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:12",
      "text": "A man void of understanding sneers at his fellow citizens: but a sensible man is quiet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:13",
      "text": "A double-tongued man discloses the secret counsels of an assembly: but he that is faithful in spirit conceals matters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:14",
      "text": "They that have no guidance fall like leaves: but in much counsel there is safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:15",
      "text": "A bad man does harm wherever he meets a just man: and he hates the sound of safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:16",
      "text": "A gracious wife brings glory to her husband: but a woman hating righteousness is a theme of dishonour. The slothful come to want: but the diligent support themselves with wealth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:17",
      "text": "A merciful man does good to his own soul: but the merciless destroys his own body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:18",
      "text": "An ungodly man performs unrighteous works: but the seed of the righteous is a reward of truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:19",
      "text": "A righteous son is born for life: but the persecution of the ungodly ends in death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:20",
      "text": "Perverse ways are an abomination to the Lord: but all they that are blameless in their ways are acceptable to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:21",
      "text": "He that unjustly strikes hands shall not be unpunished: but he that sows righteousness shall receive a faithful reward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:22",
      "text": "As an ornament in a swine's snout, so is beauty to an ill-minded woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:23",
      "text": "All the desire of the righteous is good: but the hope of the ungodly shall perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:24",
      "text": "There are some who scatter their own, and make it more: and there are some also who gather, yet have less.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:25",
      "text": "Every sincere soul is blessed: but a passionate man is not graceful. overthrow of the rebellious shall spoil them.” 11:3 Comp. Heb. 11:5 Gr. right divides. 11:10 See Appendix which gives the Alexandrine text as: “[note - Part of verse 10.]— but at the destruction of the wicked there is exultation.” 11:13 See chap 20. 27. 11:14 Or, governance. 11:16 Gr. raises. 11:16",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:26",
      "text": "May he that hoards corn leave it to the nation: but blessing be on the head of him that gives it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:27",
      "text": "He that devises good counsels seeks good favour: but as for him that seeks after evil, evil shall overtake him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:28",
      "text": "He that trusts in wealth shall fall; but he that helps righteous men shall rise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:29",
      "text": "He that deals not graciously with his own house shall inherit the wind; and the fool shall be servant to the wise man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:30",
      "text": "Out of the fruit of righteousness grows a tree of life; but the souls of transgressors are cut off before their time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.11.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:31",
      "text": "If the righteous scarcely be saved, where shall the ungodly and the sinner appear?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
